channel.title: Silab client Error messages
channel.description:
Umm.. okay, so... when i open up the silab client it comes up with these messages:
1. Unable to connet, bad session ID. 2. Unexpected server response, Please try using a different world (says this one the most). 3. Error connecting to server. 4. Your account has been disabled. Please check your message-center for details (says this one the least). ^^what message center?? the server im using?? if its the servers message center, i dont have anything i my inbox...^^
Do i need to download a new version of silab client or something? because i was clicking kinda quickly and i think it said "your silab isnt up-to-date" or something like that, anyway... help please? :confused: (these messages come up on silab client)
(BY THE WAY... its nothing to do with the server because on the website it says its online) (Yes, the online thing is updated like every nano-second, i KNOW its online)
